# Padrões de API Services

## Arquitetura de API

```
Client Components:
  API Resource (extends HttpClient) → Axios instance → Backend

Server Components (SSR):
  serverApi (fetch wrapper) → Backend (com cookies)
```

## HttpClient Base

```typescript
// lib/api/http-client.ts
class HttpClient<T> {
  constructor(protected path: string) {}

  async paginate(params?: RequestParams): Promise<Pagination<T>>
  async getAll(params?: RequestParams): Promise<T[]>
  async getById(id: number, params?: RequestParams): Promise<T>
  async create(data: Partial<T>): Promise<T>
  async update(id: number, data: Partial<T>): Promise<T>
  async delete(id: number): Promise<void>
}
```

## API Resource (por entidade)

```typescript
// lib/api/resources/orders.ts
import { HttpClient } from '../http-client'
import { api } from '../client'
import type { Order, OrderFilters, CreateOrderData } from '@/components/features/orders/types/types'

class OrdersResource extends HttpClient<Order> {
  constructor() {
    super('/orders')
  }

  // Métodos customizados
  async approve(id: number, data: ApproveData): Promise<Order> {
    const response = await api.put<Order>(`${this.path}/${id}/approve`, data)
    return response.data
  }

  async export(filters: OrderFilters): Promise<Blob> {
    const response = await api.get(`${this.path}/exports`, {
      params: filters,
      responseType: 'blob',
    })
    return response.data
  }

  async createNote(orderId: number, note: string): Promise<OrderNote> {
    const response = await api.post(`${this.path}/${orderId}/notes`, { note })
    return response.data
  }
}

// Singleton export
export const ordersResource = new OrdersResource()

// Re-export types do feature
export type { Order, OrderFilters, CreateOrderData } from '@/components/features/orders/types/types'
```

## Server-Side Fetch (SSR)

```typescript
// lib/api/server.ts
import { cookies } from 'next/headers'

const serverApi = {
  get: <T>(endpoint: string, params?: object) => serverFetch<T>(endpoint, { method: 'GET', params }),
  post: <T>(endpoint: string, data?: unknown) => serverFetch<T>(endpoint, { method: 'POST', body: data }),
}

// Uso em Server Components (pages):
async function OrdersContent() {
  const orders = await serverApi.get<Pagination<Order>>('/orders', {
    page: 1,
    perPage: 25,
    includes: orderIncludes,
  })
  return <OrdersClient orders={orders} />
}
```

- `serverApi` usa `fetch()` nativo com Next.js caching
- Lê token do cookie `redd.token` automaticamente
- Default: `revalidate: 60` (ISR 60s)

